The paper discusses the use of semantic word embeddings in natural language processing, which is a common topic in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and modeling, which suggests that it could also fit into the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of generative models, which could also place it in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
